  "body": "- [ ] I've [opened a support ticket](https://trufflesuite.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/requests/new) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\nwith truffle-config.js\r\n```js\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  networks: {\r\n    development: {\r\n      provider: () =>\r\n        new HDWalletProvider({\r\n          mnemonic: {\r\n            phrase: MNEMONIC,\r\n          },\r\n          providerOrUrl: 'http://localhost:8545',\r\n        }),\r\n      gas: 5000000,\r\n      network_id: '*', // Match any network id\r\n    },\r\n    ......\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhen I run:\r\n```bash\r\n# at first terminal\r\nganache-cli\r\n# at second terminal\r\ntruffle migrate --reset --network development --verbose-rpc\r\n```\r\nthen the second terminal will hangs at \"Deploying 'Migrations'\" every time, and the first terminal will reports many eth_blockNumber.\r\n\r\nIf I change development as below:\r\n```js\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  networks: {\r\n    development: {\r\n      host: \"localhost\",\r\n      port: 8545,\r\n      gas: 5000000,\r\n      network_id: \"*\", // Match any network id\r\n    },\r\n    ......\r\n}\r\n```\r\nThen the problem disappeared at once.\r\n \r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System:  Linux ubuntu 5.11.0-38-generic\r\n* Ethereum client: ganache-cli\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): Truffle v5.4.14 (core: 5.4.14)\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v14.18.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`):  6.14.15\r\n",
